      "description": "Hello, hello! In this episode, I chat with Jona Schlegel, who specializes in Visual Science Communication, and we discuss artifact sketching, GIS, and a range of other topics. For more information and to learn about ways you can get involved, please visit the links below."
    },
    {
      "id": "guest-2",
      "title": "The Graffiti Palimpsest (Part 1) - Ep 51",
      "show": "And My Trowel",
      "date": "2025-08-23",
      "likes": 1,
      "views": 21,
      "url": "https://www.archaeologypodcastnetwork.com/trowel/51",
      "type": "podcast",
      "description": "This episode, Ash and Tilly have a new quest from the Karnithril Collegium of Wall Lore to document vanishing graffiti. They are joined in their quest by archaeologist and visual science communicator Jona Schlegel, who shares her insight based on her previous research into graffiti along the Danube canal in Vienna. Together the three discuss those most pressing of questions: What actually is graffiti? How can you become a field archaeologist in different countries? And will Ash finally make Tilly that cup of tea?"
    },
    {
      "id": "guest-3",
      "title": "The Graffiti Palimpsest (Part 2) - Ep 52",
      "show": "And My Trowel",
      "date": "2025-09-05",
      "likes": 2,
      "views": 20,
      "url": "https://www.archaeologypodcastnetwork.com/trowel/52",
      "type": "podcast",
      "description": "In part two, Ash and Tilly continue their quest to help The Karnithril Collegium of Wall Lore record the disappearing graffiti of Thar-Vael! With expert help from archaeological illustrator and visual science communicator, Jona Schlegal, the team define the meaning of graffiti and figure out the question: are dragon’s wings the mystical equivalent of on-site sun-blocking jackets?"
    }
